m_q.target_metric: Total population for city districts where foreign nationals percentage equals 23.3%
sub_questions: Which city districts have exactly 23.3% foreign nationals?
What is the population value for those districts?
What is the sum of population across matching districts?

scale_issues: Area in km² column contains unit suffix 'km²' embedded in values
Foreign nationals in % column contains percentage symbol '%' embedded in values
Numeric columns stored as object/string type instead of numeric

format_notes: Numeric values use comma as decimal separator (European format)
Thousand separators may be present as dots
Area values include unit suffix 'km²' that needs to be stripped
Percentage values include '%' symbol that needs to be stripped
All numeric columns are stored as strings and need type conversion

constraints: Foreign nationals in % must equal exactly 23.3%
Population values must be valid positive integers
Handle potential floating point comparison issues with percentage values
derived_filters: Parse 'Foreign nationals in %' to extract numeric value without '%' symbol
Convert European decimal format (comma) to standard format (dot)
output_format_requirements: Handle case where no districts match the criteria (return 0 or null)
Handle case where multiple districts match (sum their populations)
